Following the dissolution of the National Working Committee (NWC) of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), some stakeholders within the party have urged the party stalwarts to retain chairmanship seat in the South South region. The stakeholders, under the auspices of a Non-Governmental Organisation, Power Arc Media warned that any attempt to zone national chairmanship position during next convention to another zone may cause disharmony, disaffection and adversely affect the “already troubled party”. Speaking through their director of operations in a statement, Mr. Tedd Avindigh, the stakeholders zoning the position from the south would create a sense of loss and would ultimately be counterproductive to the party. APC zones national chairmanship to South South So who’ll be APC national chairman? APC  leaders renew efforts to counter governors on zoning